HEADWORD: Protuberate
<hw>Pro*tu"ber*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>protuberare</ets>; <ets>pro</ets> forward + <ets>tuber</ets> a
hump, protuberance. See <er>Tuber</er>.]</ety> <def>To swell, or be
prominent, beyond the adjacent surface; to bulge out.</def> <rj><au>S.
Sharp.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

